  <title>I can not SHIFT+Drag to Spin (or CTRL+Drag to Pan) the model</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>FAQs<keyword>Why can&apos;t I Spin or Pan the model with the Drag technique?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">FAQ: I can not SHIFT+Drag to Spin (or CTRL+Drag to Pan) the model. Why?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">If you preselect an element, for example, a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Plane</text>, you will find you cannot <text styleclass="VariableName">Spin</text> or <text styleclass="VariableName">Pan</text> your model with the <text styleclass="VariableName">Drag technique</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Make sure your mouse-pointer (cursor) is not above any other element before you <text styleclass="VariableName">Mouse-Button-Down</text> to start to drag.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Note</text>: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We recommend you use your keyboard arrow keys to Spin the model - <text styleclass="SeeAlso">see more : </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Keyboard-Shortcuts" styleclass="SeeAlso">Keyboard shortcuts</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
  </body>
</topic>
